        <title>Taking a closer look</title>
        <content>&lt;p&gt;Now that you understand what WIOA workforce preparation activities are and why they are important to incorporate into all levels of adult education, let’s take a closer look at the underlying skills and competencies in more detail than the WIOA legislation provides. We’ll also look at how workforce preparation activities align with research on strategies for effective instruction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you read about the workforce preparation activities and accompanying classroom examples, you’ll notice that the skills overlap and are mutually reinforcing. That is, the attainment of one is helpful or necessary in acquiring another. They are rarely taught, practiced, or applied to real-world situations in isolation, though a specific skill might be emphasized or highlighted more explicitly over another.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;Throughout this section, classroom examples are provided to show how workforce preparation skills are integrated in familiar settings. These examples reflect using a combination of workforce preparation activities to develop rich lessons.  &lt;/p&gt;
