        <title>Basic academic skills</title>
        <content>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/OG_BasicAcademic.jpg" width="550" height="385" usemap="navmap" style="float: left;" alt="Workforce preparation skills and competencies graphic, which include Skills: basic academic skills, critical thinking, digital literacy and self-management, and competencies: utilizing resources, using information, working with others, understanding systems, skills necessary for successful transition into and completion of postsecondary education or employment" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;map name="navmap"&gt; 
&lt;area name="Exploring workforce preparation skills" shape="rect" coords="214,1,339,23" href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1101@$" alt="Link to exploring workforce preparation skills" title="Link to exploring workforce preparation skills" target="_top" /&gt;
 
&lt;area name="Basic Academic Skills" shape="rect" coords="1,29,547,81" href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1102@$" alt="Link to Basic Academic Skills" title="Link to Basic Academic Skills" target="_top" /&gt;
 &lt;/map&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Academic skills - reading, writing, math/numeracy, and English language skills - are the foundation for workforce preparation activities. The emphasis here is on applying academic skills: problems or tasks are rarely encountered in our home or work lives that present themselves as they were presented in classrooms or textbooks. To deepen learning and prepare for the workforce, academic skills and content knowledge must also be thoughtfully applied and put to practical use in the workplace and elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the passage of WIOA, the scope of adult education is broadened to incorporate strategies and services that help learners prepare for and succeed in college and careers. A focus on workforce preparation activities requires educators to emphasize the application and transferability of academic skills to a variety of contexts that are relevant to students’ education and career goals and the skills needed to attain those goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we’ll see when we explore the full array of workforce preparation activities, such activities involve skills that are mutually reinforcing and complementary when integrated with academic skill building.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #693300; font-family: Verdana; font-size: small;" color="#693300" face="Verdana" p="" size="2"&gt;Click the arrow to continue to &lt;a href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1103@$"&gt;What research says about integrating basic academic skills&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
