        <title>Classroom activity example: Contextualized basic academic skills</title>
        <content>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width="550" height="386" alt=" Workforce preparation skills and competencies graphic, which include Skills: basic academic skills, critical thinking, digital literacy and self-management, and competencies: utilizing resources, using information, working with others, understanding systems, skills necessary for successful transition into and completion of postsecondary education or employment" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/OG_BasicAcademic.jpg" usemap="#navmap" /&gt; &lt;map name="navmap"&gt; 
&lt;area title="Link to Workforce Preparation Activities" href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1101@$" coords="3,25,469,70" target="_top" alt="Link to Basic Academic Skills" name="Workforce Preparation Activities" /&gt;
 
&lt;area title="" href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1101@$" shape="rect" coords="174,170,376,199" alt="" name="Link to WPSC Graphic" /&gt;
 
&lt;area title="" href="$@BOOKVIEWBYIDCH*6297*1101@$" shape="rect" coords="207,1,336,30" alt="" name="Link to WPSC Graphic" /&gt;
 &lt;/map&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;Here is a classroom example of contextualized basic academic skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In a unit on finding employment, intermediate ESOL students:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;write job interview questions and role-play them in pairs to practice WH questions (who, what, where, why, why);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;use examples of real employee handbooks to practice reading strategies, such as inferencing from headings and picture/diagrams, background knowledge, and finding the main idea; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;identify unfamiliar vocabulary words to learn.&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #693300; font-family: Verdana; font-size: small;" size="2" face="Verdana" color="#693300"&gt;Click on &lt;strong&gt;SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt; in the WPSC graphic to explore more workforce preparation skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
