      <chapter id="1106">
        <pagenum>7</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>What the research says about integrating critical thinking skills</title>
        <content>&lt;p&gt;Explicit, &lt;a href="$@GLOSSARYVIEWBYID*6319@$&amp;amp;mode=letter&amp;amp;hook=S&amp;amp;sortkey=&amp;amp;sortorder=asc" target="_blank"&gt;scaffolded instruction &lt;/a&gt;is important for learning and applying new knowledge, because it helps learners develop complex strategies in combination with content knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Critical thinking, and the questioning techniques at its root, are a&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;s much a key strategy in the &lt;i&gt;process&lt;/i&gt; of deeper learning as it is an outcome of workforce preparation activities. Again, workforce preparation activities a&lt;/span&gt;nd effective content instruction can mutually reinforce skills that are important to learning as well as to the workplace (Lesgold, A. &amp;amp; Welch-Ross, M. eds., 2012. p. 129).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
