&lt;p&gt;Here is a classroom example that involves critical thinking as well as skills for transitioning to employment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, the teacher guides the class through a brainstorm to identify work values (e.g., flexibility versus consistency, working independently versus as part of a team, work at a desk versus physical labor). Next, the students complete a prioritization activity to identify their top job values. After gathering information about an occupation of interest to them, they use a rubric to assess the extent to which the occupation seems to align with their top five priority values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p class="MoreInfoBox"&gt;Explore the TEAL Fact Sheet on &lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/sites/default/files/12_TEAL_Deeper_Learning_Qs_complete_5_1_0.pdf" target="_parent"&gt;Deeper Learning&lt;/a&gt; for information, strategies, and examples of deeper learning instructional techniques.&lt;/p&gt;
