 &lt;/map&gt;&lt;map name="navmap"&gt; &lt;/map&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is how one ABE teacher incorporates digital literacy as well as self-management skills into her classroom instruction:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Students learn how to use excel to set-up a spreadsheet that they will use to track how they spend their time for a week. They learn how to open and save a document; how to create a table with column headings such as work, transportation, school, meals, and chores; and how to enter time, in minutes, into the cells. After they log their time for a week, they learn how to set up a formula for adding cells and calculating average time spent per task per week. Then students analyze how they spend their time and see if they can find 45 minutes per week for additional reading. Finally, they discuss the concept of spreadsheets and other uses for them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
