      <chapter id="1114">
        <pagenum>15</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Classroom activity example: Self-management and using information</title>
        <content>&lt;p&gt;Here is an example that incorporates self-management skills and using information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Students create a log to track how they allocate their time for transportation, school, work, sleep, meals, household chores, television, reading, etc. In class, they analyze the results and discuss whether they can dedicate an additional 45 minutes per week for homework to progress more rapidly in class. During class, students develop a study schedule and commit to following it for four weeks. Each week, students meet in small groups to discuss challenges to sticking with the schedule and possible solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/10179262_m.jpg" width="550" height="366" alt="Adult students writing in a schedule log" style="vertical-align: text-bottom;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
